  "decision": "Not accepted",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed but all credibility factor gaps remain. A screening sensitivity study was conducted informally to rank input parameters by their influence on the hemolysis index; results indicated that rotor speed and gap clearance dominate output variance. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all with achieved levels below required levels), 6 factors not assessed (flagged as epistemic gaps at MRL 5). Decision: Not accepted.",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
